<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5288&amp;p=47839#p47839"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Language definitions for syntax highlighting in Notepad++]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5288&amp;p=47839#p47839"><![CDATA[
I used notepad++ to create a language definition file for ppmck mml. This means that as you type mml keywords, notepad++ will highlight the terms. I used four different colors, one for each classification of keyword. You have to download my userdefinelanguage.xml file and overwrite your file in notepad++.<br /><br />Notepad++:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://notepad-plus.sourceforge.net/uk/site.htm">http://notepad-plus.sourceforge.net/uk/site.htm</a><!-- m --><br /><br />A good tutorial to "install" my definition file:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://weblogs.asp.net/jgalloway/archive/2006/11/25/creating-a-user-defined-language-in-notepad.aspx">http://weblogs.asp.net/jgalloway/archiv ... tepad.aspx</a><!-- m --><br /><br />My userdefinelanguage file:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.sendspace.com/file/2p55zl">http://www.sendspace.com/file/2p55zl</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3613">Fib Gibbley</a> — Tue Jun 09, 2009 2:19 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
